<plot>Everything and Nothing creates an intimate dialogue that weaves back and forth between representations of a figure (of resistance) and subject. The film features interviews with Soha Bechara, an ex-Lebanese National Resistance fighter. She is interviewed in her Paris dorm room after release from captivity in the El-Khiam torture and interrogation center in South Lebanon where she had been detained for 10 years, 6 of which she spent in isolation.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?184598</url></doc>
